NOSP - Norwegian Forum for Offshore Survey and Positioning

NOSP Statutes
Norwegian forum for Offshore Survey and Positioning  (NOSP) is a non-profit forum established in 2013 with the intention to drive forward the offshore survey community in Norway through:

- Providing a platform for social interaction, networking and information exchange;
- Raising the profile of the offshore survey community within the offshore sector;
- Representing the survey profession to universities and other educational institutions.

A SUL FLORESTAS GEO ENGENHARIA LTDA foi fundada no ano de 2012 por três engenheiros florestais que tinham como objetivo empreender por meio da prestação de serviços diferenciados para empresas florestais.

Missão: Facilitar a gestão dos negócios de nossos clientes empregando geoprocessamento.

Visão: Ser reconhecida como uma empresa de excelência no desenvolvimento de soluções geotecnológicas e inovadoras.

Valores:
Respeito, compromisso e honestidade | resulta em uma relação construtiva entre empresa, colaboradores e clientes.
Tecnologia, simplicidade e objetividade | garante o sucesso de soluções inovadoras e produtos diferenciados.
Capacitação, agilidade e qualidade | da segurança para contratação dos serviços e garantia de satisfação do cliente.
Responsabilidade Social, meio ambiente e solidez | viabiliza o crescimento sustentado.

São alguns serviços de destaque: 
	Levantamento com VANT;
	Georreferenciamento de imóveis rurais;
	Mapeamento de uso e ocupação do solo; 
	Inventário florestal;
	Diagnóstico para adequação ambiental de propriedades rurais; 
	Execução de processos de due diligence; 
	Estudos ambientais; 
	Elaboração de planos e programas ambientais;
	Monitoramento ambiental.

Acquisition, validation, conservation et restitution des connaissances géologiques de base relative à la géologie du pays au profit des activités économiques ;
Élaboration du programme national d’infrastructure géologique en matière de cartes géologiques régulières, de cartes géophysiques et géochimiques régionales ;
Réalisation, supervision et contrôle de travaux d’infrastructure géologique 
Publication officielle des documents et cartes géologiques régulières et thématiques et leur diffusion nationale et internationale.

Beyond Measure Surveying offers professional surveying services across all aspects of engineering and construction.  Our services include;
                  •	Contour and Detail Surveys;
                  •	BOQ verifications;
                  •	Machine guidance file creation and upload; 
                  •	Construction set-out;
                  •	As constructed and Conformance surveys;
                  •	End of month quantity surveys;
                  •	3D Laser Scanning & modelling;
                  •	UAV surveys

With more than 15 years in the surveying industry, Julie concluded the time was right to challenge herself and grow her passion for surveying through running her own business, servicing the region she loves and calls home, thus Beyond Measure Surveying was brought to life.

At Beyond Measure Surveying, we’re passionate about safety and getting the best result for our clients.  We continue to adopt new technologies with a vision to optimise productivity and turn-around times for our clients whilst being able to ensure the safety of our staff.  We endeavour to expand our services to the region, exploring new technologies as they come to market.

All of our staff are registered with the Surveyors Board of QLD and we are working our way to Cadastral and Consulting Endorsements to allow us to expand into cadastral survey work in the near future.  

Contact us at: julie@bmsurveying.com.au or message this page.

GEO-BASES is a full-service surveying & mapping, spatial planning & environmental management firm that provides supports on a number of land governance, urban regeneration and institutional mandates for clients and at enhancing efficiency in public service delivery in areas of:

-	Field Acquisition of Geospatial Data and Statistical Dataset;
-	Full implementation of Geographic Information Systems (GIS); 
-	Deformation Studies and Socio-Economic Impact Assessment (SEIA); 
-	Land Consolidation, Land Use, Land Audit, Land Rights & Tenure Security; 
-	Spatial Data Infrastructures (SDIs) & Geospatial Information Frameworks (IGIF);
-	Urban Planning, City Renewal & Regeneration, Slum Upgrading & Landscape Architecture.

GEO-BASES offers comprehensive and complementary range of surveying options and geospatial solutions that are backed by time-honoured techniques, high fidelity tools and high-definition technologies in drafting, driving and delivering one-off private jobs and or much larger corporate briefs designated as standalone contracts, as well as complex multi-sectoral interventions and/or social initiatives screened for and structured as Public Private Partnership (PPP) projects.

GEO-BASES’ team of key and non-key experts holding professional licensure and certification do undertake field and desk research, give expert opinions and reviews, and provide advisory and ratings on land and land-based investments, infrastructures and instruments to a select but broad clienteles that include individuals & corporate bodies, MNCs & MDBs, local communities and non-governmental organisations, and subnational & central governments.

As contractor and consultant of choice in our area of specialties, we match our rapidly expanding portfolio with clear understanding of clients’ requests and requiremensts in ways that prevent any confusion or delay in the interpretation and execution of contracts; such that projects run more smoothly, remain on schedule and stay within budget.

The IWO Group is an international specialist in professional surveying, precise data collection and analysis, as well as customised software solutions for geodata. Our mission is to provide reliable and high-quality topographical models that your entire company can work with across disciplines. We use modern technologies and standardised procedures, and build on 30 years of experience in the stone and quarry industry. Our commitment to quality is to be precise, effective, efficient and innovative.

OUR PORTFOLIO
includes individual and specialised services in four business areas:

// IWO Survey: Surveying services 
Aerial, marine, terrestrial and underground surveying 
using the latest surveying technologies and techniques

// IWO Data: Data processing and analysis
Creation of 3D maps, data calculation and evaluation

// IWO Software: Software solutions 
Web-based access, storage, processing and presentation of corporate and geodata / central platform for communications and project management

// IWO Consulting: Consulting and training 
Professional consulting and client support for geodata and surveying projects worldwide

